ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-11-29T15:55:12Z\u0022 title=\u002211/29/2023 03:55  PM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Nov 29\u0022\u003ENovember 29, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Aeolica\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Aeolica","CreatedById":227199,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-11-29T16:25:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy largest practical \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E \u0022Elephant Foot\u0022, KLO payload around 520t.\u003Cbr\u003E\n9 \u0022Mammoth II\u0022 \u002B 8 \u0022Vector\u0022 engines provide a sea-level thrust of 4006t\u003Cbr\u003E\nAfter losing all the reinforcing struts, it can land intact on the sea or flat ground!\u003Cimg alt=\u0022C.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002286.42\u0022 height=\u0022864\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/nw2w4VK/C.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022E.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002286.92\u0022 height=\u0022867\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/Q8gc7QY/E.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022F.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002277.67\u0022 height=\u0022687\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/jy04s0S/F.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022G.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002280.25\u0022 height=\u0022746\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/zZxjsRr/G.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022B.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002282.67\u0022 height=\u0022689\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/s62y7YM/B.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022H.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002281.92\u0022 height=\u0022672\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/LPFdtjD/H.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022I.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002279.50\u0022 height=\u0022708\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/BKqydPH/I.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022J.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002281.75\u0022 height=\u0022682\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/xJvCBB3/J.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022K.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002280.50\u0022 height=\u0022671\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.ibb.co/KmtfMbq/K.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-11-29T16:35:20Z\u0022 title=\u002211/29/2023 04:35  PM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Nov 29\u0022\u003ENovember 29, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Aeolica\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bej Kerman","CreatedById":182413,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-11-29T17:26:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224343551\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022221014\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221701272017\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022227199\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Aeolica\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Aeolica said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe vessel must be an\u00A0\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E in the original game.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nThe assembly anchor must be on the cargo (the reinforcing struts of the cargo must be intact).\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThese rules seem a bit pointless if you don\u0027t mind the criticism.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Aeolica","CreatedById":227199,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-11-29T18:09:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224343570\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022221014\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221701278805\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022182413\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bej Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n49 minutes ago, Bej Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThese rules seem a bit pointless if you don\u0027t mind the criticism.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI just wrote a patent application and am still thinking in the legal manner.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nHowever, I don\u0027t consider these rules to be pointless. For instance, concerning the assembly anchor, the current mechanism in the game is that detaching the decoupler, separator or docking port will result in all downstream struts being disconnected. In other words, you have to choose between let your cargo (giant space station/interstellar spacecraft) lose all struts or let your \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E lose all struts.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think a successful landing with a 425-ton empty\u00A0\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E without any strut is\u00A0\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#374151;font-size:16px;\u0022\u003Ealready close to the engineering limit\u003C/span\u003E. In fact, I tried to build an \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E with\u00A0\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Low Kerbin Orbit\u0022\u003E\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Low Kerbin Orbit\u0022\u003ELKO\u003C/abbr\u003E\u003C/abbr\u003E payload of 1500 tons, but it has to retain struts and sacrifice struts of its cargo; otherwise, it would disintegrate upon landing.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-11-29T18:17:04Z\u0022 title=\u002211/29/2023 06:17  PM\u0022 data-short=\u0022Nov 29\u0022\u003ENovember 29, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by Aeolica\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}